Where, α represented the number of absorption coefficient, cm−1;
                        h was Planck constant, J-S; ν stood for incident light frequency, Hz;
                        A was constant;
                        Eg
                         represented the band gap width, eV;
                        n was related to the type of optical transition in the catalyst. The test samples were all indirect transitions, n = 4.
